eachus@spectre.mitre.org (Robert I. Eachus) writes:
> 
>    The two problems are equivalent in that, if you can factor in
> polynomial time, then you can find discrete logs in polynomial time
> and vice-versa.
> 
> --
> 
> 					Robert I. Eachus
> 

But, in PGP... given clear text, x, encrypted m=x^e mod n, you are trying 
to find e'th roots (not logs) (I Guess if one encrypted x as m'=g^x mod n, 
then you WOULD be trying to find logs mod n with respt to base g)

